介绍（论证、讲话等的）要点
data.enText: to show clearly the way that an argument, a speech, etc. will develop

means: 介绍(论证、讲话等的)要点

tr: a post bearing a sign that gives directions or shows the way
mark with a signpost, as of a path

value.def: A signpost is a sign where roads meet that tells you which direction to go in to reach a particular place or different places.

example.ex: The lights of the car lit up a signpost...
Turn off at the signpost for Attlebridge.
example.tran: 在路标处拐弯去往阿特尔桥。

value.def: A signpost is something that helps you to know how a situation or a course of action will develop.

example.ex: The outcome of tomorrow's elections will be studied carefully as a signpost of voter intentions on the really big day this year...
example.tran: 明天的选举结果会被作为今年大选的选民意愿风向标来仔细研究。

example.ex: These events were all signposts pointing toward change.
example.tran: 这些事件都是将要进行变革的征兆。
